declarations.description:
Components Page Object Model

This object model includes basic functionalities like setup, teardown, mount, etc.
used for Momentum components E2E testing
declarations.name: ComponentsPage

members.name: setup
members.description:
**Setup function**

to run before the test to navigate correctly

members.name: tearDown
members.description:
**TearDown function**

to run after the test

members.name: navigate
members.description:
**Navigate function**

Path urls are allowed

If no url provided, it navigates to baseURL

- Go to the provided url
- Await till page has been loaded

declarations.description: Contains common `accessibility` utils, which are useful when doing accessibility tests
declarations.name: Accessibility

members.name: attachA11yResults
members.description:
Attaches the provided scan results as JSON
to the test report

members.name: checkForA11yViolations
members.description:
Checks for Accessibility violations by scanning the whole
page with axe-core, using the specific accessibility WCAG tags to check
and disabled rules. The results will be attached as a JSON file
to the test report afterwards.

This function will fail if there are any accessibility violations.

members.name: pressAndCheckFocus

parameters.name: keyToPress
parameters.description: key which should be pressed

parameters.name: elementsToBeFocused
parameters.description: array of elements, which have to be focused after pressing a key

members.description:
pressAndCheckFocus utility function - it will press the provided `keyToPress` as often
as the provided `elementsToBeFocused` are and checks afterwards, if the provided element of the
`elementsToBeFocused` has been focused.

If only 1 keyPress needs to be done, just simply provide the `elementsToBeFocused` array with
1 element, which should receive focus.
